		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=7899"><span id=Scholar>Chimi</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>18 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Hmm...you have all your combat skills maxed out but you use no weapons...that's quite a feat, how's that done exactly? Point being you have to either have blunt weapons or only have your hand to hand and special attack skills maxed out.<br><br>If it's the first case, you have little to worry about. Save up some cash and get yourself some of the fine blunts offered to us monks. Be it fighting batons, saps of piety, canes of tranquil,... whatever, these buddhistic chopsticks make us monks quite the turbo-charged carnage dealers. Some of the best blunts in the game are monk only. Most of these blunts are not only light wieght but have an excellent delay to damage ratio as well.<br><br>Now if it's the later case, tsk...tsk...tsk. You really need to master those blunt combat skills. A monks bread and butter for a long while is the set of chopsticks he or she has in hand. So...get yourself the lowest delay ( don't worry about damage so much, as the faster you hit the faster your skill rises ) blunts you can get your calloused hands on and prepare to play the drums on the many Mobs to come. Master those skills and you will see a nice whirlwind effect when you enter combat. You beat a Mob 4 times before anyone else touches it. That is relish.<br><br>As a side note, I hope you're not one of those holier than thou monks who feel that only a "true monk" would just use his or her fists and feel like they stand on some imaginary pedistal in the sky because "they don't use weapons".... Please. I understand the roleplaying aspect of the game and rather enjoy it. But if you "choose" not to use weapons as a roleplaying tool for your monk, then you have no right to complain. You chose. If you wanna keep up with the rest of the classes of your level, use the means to which they gave you to achieve that goal. Use the blunts. Master the blunts. With that, still keep your hand to hand maxed out as well, because I believe after a certain high level your paws actually out-damage per second the blunts.<br><br>A monk without weapons is like a broken jawed hooker secured in a chastity belt. You can only do so much with your hands.<br><br>-Chimi, the master of bad analogies.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >5 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
